Round 1:
[Patient] Can you recommend exercises for me? 
[Healthcare Educator] Walking, swimming, and biking are great for heart health.

Round 2:
[Patient] How often should I exercise? 
[Healthcare Educator] Aim for at least 30 minutes of moderate exercise most days.

Round 3:
[Patient] Can I do strength training too? 
[Healthcare Educator] Yes, strength training can help improve your overall fitness.

Round 4:
[Patient] Should I avoid any exercises? 
[Healthcare Educator] Avoid high-intensity exercises that may strain your heart.

Round 5:
[Patient] What about yoga or tai chi? 
[Healthcare Educator] Yoga and tai chi can help improve flexibility and reduce stress.

Round 6:
[Patient] Should I monitor my heart rate? 
[Healthcare Educator] Yes, keep an eye on your heart rate during exercise.

Round 7:
[Patient] Can I exercise outside in my neighborhood? 
[Healthcare Educator] Yes, as long as it's safe and you're comfortable.

Round 8:
[Patient] Can I exercise with friends or family? 
[Healthcare Educator] Exercising with loved ones can be motivating and fun.

Round 9:
[Patient] How can I stay motivated to exercise? 
[Healthcare Educator] Set achievable goals and track your progress to stay motivated.

Round 10:
[Patient] Thank you for the exercise recommendations! 
[Healthcare Educator] You're welcome! Stay active and take care of your heart.